The median sales price for the Oak Knoll-Edgewood Park area is $1,527,500. The $1,659,400 estimated value is 10.63% greater than the median listing price of $1,500,000 for the Oak Knoll-Edgewood Park area.
According to the Redwood City public records, the property at 106 Westgate St, Redwood City, CA 94062 has approximately 1,550 square feet, 4 beds and 2 baths with a lot size of 3,700 square feet. Nearby schools include John Gill Elementary School, John F. Kennedy Middle School and Woodside High School. Comparable nearby homes for sale include 20 Echo Ln, 221 Topaz St and 1580 Cordilleras Rd.

posts.html: Beautiful single story hilltophideaway home on 1 acre with spectacular panoramic bay views located on a private and secluded street! Entry leads into a large living room with a cozy fireplace and floor to ceiling windows for your bay view enjoyment. Long hallway with viewsto the atrium leads you to the Family Room with another fireplace and indoor bbq. Spacious eat in kitchen features two ovens, dishwasher, electric cooktop, trash compactor and a pantry. Formal dining room. This home features 4 spacious bedrooms. Master Bedroom Suite features dual sinks, a long counter, mirrors abound and a large his and hers walk-in closet! Every bedroom in the house has an attached bathroom! Three full bathrooms and two 1/2 baths for guests. LaundryRoom and Office.Back yard features a private pool and spa, an attrium with water feature and lots of space to entertain. Detached 3 car garage with added storage room. Hollywood driveway and side access on both sides of the home.

posts.html:
Listed for $1,748,000

This warm inviting home is located in the wonderful Mt. Carmel neighborhood. Living room features a stunning marble slab fireplace with custom mantel and picture windows. Oak flooring has been refinished to bring out its natural beauty and luster. Dining room, kitchen and family room flow gently into each other in the open floor plan. Updated kitchen features wood cabinetry, quartz counters and an imported tile backsplash. Sun filled, spacious family room with new carpeting. Large master suite with private bath and walk-in closet. Master bath features glass accents, soaking tub, and heated stone floors. Freshly updated hall bathroom with tile floors and tub surround. Convenient laundry room with full-size appliances and garage access. Central AC and leased solar panels for low cost energy. Attached one-car garage. Private backyard includes low maintenance composite deck, patio, and lawn area surrounded by raised brick beds with flowing plants. Freshly painted inside and out.

100K Price Reduction! Sunny 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom home in the sought-after Mt. Carmel neighborhood. From the front porch to the secluded backyard patio, this well appointed home welcomes relaxing and entertaining. Enjoy your master suite with sliding doors to the backyard, as well as a large bathroom with walk in shower. Highlights include hardwood floors, fresh paint throughout, upgraded kitchen, new gas fireplaces in the living room and den, large windows, central AC, ceiling fans, Nest thermostat, Nest Protect (for CO2), Ring front door, and a low maintenance back yard with separate patios and a 124 SF tuff shed. 1, 750 SF per Realist 6/19/19 and 1, 805 SF per Floor Plan Visuals. 1 mile or less to bustling downtown Redwood City, Stafford Park & Whole Foods. Easily accessible to 101 and 280.
